Package: RateScape
Title: Detecting and Explaining Rate Heterogeneity in Discrete Character Evolution
Version: 3.0.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Heath", "Blackmon", role = c("aut", "cre"),
         email = "h-blackmon@tamu.edu",
         comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5433-4036")),
  person("Claude", "Opus", role = "ctb", comment = "AI-assisted implementation")
  )
Description: RateScape provides Bayesian and maximum likelihood methods for
  detecting, explaining, and visualizing rate heterogeneity in discrete
  character evolution across phylogenetic trees. The package implements a
  spike-and-slab mixture model with reversible-jump MCMC for branch-specific
  rate estimation, supporting phylogenetic smoothing priors, covariate-driven
  rate models, rate-heterogeneous stochastic character mapping, and posterior
  predictive model adequacy checks. Version 3.0 adds correlated discrete trait
  evolution (Pagel's test with rate heterogeneity), constrained Q-matrix models
  (ordered, Dollo, meristic, custom constraints, rate classes), RJMCMC over
  Q-matrix structure with posterior inclusion probabilities, automatic model
  discovery across the full model space, and Felsenstein's threshold model for
  multistate discrete characters via data augmentation MCMC.
